SIMPLE: middling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Middling
<hw>Mid"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of middle rank,
state, size, or quality; about equally distant from the extremes;
medium; moderate; mediocre; ordinary.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A town of but
<xex>middling</xex> size.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hallam.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Plainly furnished, as beseemed the <qex>middling</qex>
circumstances of its inhabitants.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mid"dling*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mid"dling*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Middlings</ent>⟦br⟧
